response:
 To find out how many pounds of apples George Adrian picked in 3 hours, we'll follow these steps:
1. Calculate the rate of apple picking per hour (\textit{r}) by dividing the total pounds picked by the time in hours.
2. Use the rate (\textit{r}) to find the pounds picked in 3 hours (\textit{p}).

\textbf{Step 1:} Calculate the rate (\textit{r}):
\begin{align*}
r &= \frac{15,832~\text{pounds}}{8~\text{hours}} \\
r &= 1,979~\text{pounds per hour}
\end{align*}

\textbf{Step 2:} Calculate the pounds picked in 3 hours (\textit{p}):
\begin{align*}
p &= r \times \text{Time} \\
p &= 1,979~\text{pounds per hour} \times 3~\text{hours} \\
p &= 5,937~\text{pounds}
\end{align*}
Therefore, George Adrian picked 5,937 pounds of apples in 3 hours. <answer> 5,937 pounds </answer>

